---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Parallax Plugin">
  <h1>Parallax</h1>
  <p class="lead">Applies a <code>translate3d</code> offset to elements inside each slide as the slider scrolls, creating a depth parallax effect. The offset is proportional to each slide's distance from the active index and the configured depth.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} parallax {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>selector</code></td><td><code>string</code></td><td><code>'[data-parallax]'</code></td><td>CSS selector for elements inside each slide that receive the parallax transform.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>depth</code></td><td><code>number</code></td><td><code>0.3</code></td><td>Fraction of the slide width applied as the parallax offset. Higher values produce more pronounced movement.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>CSS overshoot</h2>
  <p>Because parallax elements shift relative to their slide, their container must be wider than 100% to avoid clipping. The overshoot needed on each side equals the depth value as a percentage:</p>
  <pre><code>{`/* depth: 0.15 — each adjacent slide's element moves 15% of slide width */
[data-parallax] {
  position: absolute;
  left: -15%;
  width: 130%; /* 100% + 2 × 15% */
  height: 100%;
}

/* depth: 0.3 (default) */
[data-parallax] {
  position: absolute;
  left: -30%;
  width: 160%; /* 100% + 2 × 30% */
  height: 100%;
}`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>{`<!-- HTML -->
<div id="my-slider">
  <div class="slide" style="position:relative; overflow:hidden;">
    <img data-parallax src="/bg-1.jpg" style="position:absolute; left:-30%; width:160%; height:100%; object-fit:cover;" />
    <span>Slide 1</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- JS -->
import { createSlider } from '@andresclua/sliderkit'
import { parallax } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'

createSlider('#my-slider', {
  plugins: [parallax({ depth: 0.3 })],
})`}</code></pre>

  <p><a href="/demos/parallax-css">View parallax demo</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
